# BaseCamp Context

This repository is linked to a BaseCamp project. Use these paths and keys whenever BaseCamp context is needed.

- BaseCamp project: `~/Desktop/CCC/BaseCamp/clients/internal/projects/generator-ccc`
- BaseCamp client: `~/Desktop/CCC/BaseCamp/clients/internal`
- Client slug: `internal`
- Project slug: `generator-ccc`
- Jira project: `SP`
- Project anchor epic: (none)
- Client umbrella epic: `SP-938`

## How To Use BaseCamp From This Repo

- To READ BaseCamp context (todos, decisions, notes, Jira keys, client metadata), use the `check-basecamp` skill. It is read-mostly and will not modify BaseCamp.
- To WRITE BaseCamp updates (todos, decisions, meeting notes, project metadata, Jira ticket filing, status changes), use the `update-basecamp` skill. It enforces BaseCamp conventions in the linked BaseCamp repo.
- Tickets created from work in this repo MUST use Jira project `SP`. Prefer the project anchor epic (none) when set; otherwise fall back to the client umbrella epic `SP-938` if set; otherwise file with no epic. Never invent a Jira project key.
- Todos belonging to this repo's work live in `~/Desktop/CCC/BaseCamp/clients/internal/projects/generator-ccc/todos.md`, in one of the three sections `## In Progress`, `## Backlog`, `## Done`. Do NOT create a root `TODO.md` in this repo for BaseCamp-tracked work.

## Write-Back Nudge

After completing meaningful work in this repo — a ticket finished, a decision made,
meeting notes captured, or a milestone reached — run `update-basecamp` before ending
the session to persist changes back to BaseCamp (`todos.md`, `decisions.md`, meeting
notes, or frontmatter). Do not rely on end-of-day automation alone; update BaseCamp
as you go when the outcome is clear.

## Project-Specific Notes

- Jira project `SP` requires Story Points (`customfield_10004`) on create; default to `1`.
- The legacy Yeoman generator under `generators/` is reference-only and out of scope.
